OL,4,Cbid by man wrongly jailed for 38 years
OL,6,FResponding, Lord Ponsonby said: "We
OL,7,Fwould encourage Mr Sullivan to make an
OL,8,Fapplication to the miscarriages of
OL,9,Fjustice application service, and we
OL,10,Fwill prioritise his application
OL,11,Fbecause of the length of the prison
OL,12,Fsentence."
OL,14,FTory peer Lord Garnier, who previously
OL,15,Fserved as solicitor general, stressed
OL,16,Fthe urgent need to appoint a chair of
OL,17,Fthe CCRC "not in the near future, but
OL,18,Ftoday".
OL,26,@nD@aOUtD@JO]yD@JOUzD@FO]
